Common Semantic HTML Tags

1.<header>
Represents the top section of a page.
Example:
                        <header>
                          <h1>My Website</h1>
                          <p>Welcome to my blog</p>
                        </header>
Usually contains:
logo
title

2.navigation
<nav>
Represents navigation links.
Example:
                            <nav>
                              <a href="#">Home</a>
                              <a href="#">About</a>
                              <a href="#">Contact</a>
                            </nav>
Used for menus.

3.<main>
Represents the main content of the page.
Example:
                                <main>
                                  <h2>Latest Articles</h2>
                                  <p>This is the main content.</p>
                                </main>
Important rule:
A page should usually have only one <main> element.

4.<article>
Used for independent content like:
blog posts
news articles
forum posts
Example:
                                  <article>
                                    <h2>HTML Basics</h2>
                                    <p>This article explains HTML.</p>
                                  </article>


5.<section>
Represents a group of related content.
Example:
                                    <section>
                                      <h2>Our Services</h2>
                                      <p>We provide web development.</p>
                                    </section>


<footer>
Represents the bottom part of the webpage.
Example:
                                          <footer>
                                            <p>© 2026 My Website</p>
                                          </footer>
Usually contains:
copyright
contact info
links

